---
title: Meatloaf A La Mom with Roasted Root Veggies and Thyme Gravy
description: It’s commonly agreed that no one makes meatloaf quite like Mom. But our chefs will settle for second best by taking a page from her book and passing on this recipe that stays about as true to tradition as can be. These ground beef mini loaves are brushed with a ketchup glaze, served with tender roasted carrots and potatoes, and drizzled with an herby thyme gravy. If you’re a mom (or pop) who wants to claim this recipe as your own, don’t worry—we’ll stay mum.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/meatloaf-a-la-mom-4b8ec989.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/meatloaf-a-la-mom-d485c085.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/meatloaf-a-la-mom-590c7d24d56afa5031551c73
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 670 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve and peel @shallot{1%tube}. Grate one half with a #box grater{} into a #medium bowl{}. Mince other half. Strip @thyme{1/4%oz}(leaves stripped from stems and chopped) from stems; discard stems. Roughly chop leaves. Halve @carrot{8%oz} lengthwise. Peel @russet potato{1}, then cut into long, thin sticks (like French fries).

Toss carrots with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and arrange toward one side of a #baking sheet{}. Toss potato with a drizzle of olive oil and arrange toward other side. Season both with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender and browned, ~{20-25%minutes} total (we'll be adding more ingredients to the sheet before the veggies are done roasting).

Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @ground beef{10%oz}, half the thyme, garlic, and a few dashes of salt and pepper to #bowl{} with shallot (we used ¾ tsp kosher salt). Gently combine with hands, then form mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves.

After veggies have roasted ~{7-8%minutes}, remove sheet from oven. Give veggies a toss. Place meatloaves on same sheet, and then brush tops of loaves with @ketchup{1%tbsp} (we sent more). Return sheet to oven and continue roasting until meatloaves are cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes} more.

> TIP: If your sheet is crowded, you can add the meatloaves to a second sheet.

== Thyme Gravy ==

Melt @butter{1/2%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add minced shallot and remaining thyme. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Sprinkle @flour{1%tbsp} into pan, stirring vigorously to combine. Whisk in @beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a simmer and let bubble until thick and saucy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice meatloaves crosswise and divide between plates. Add veggies to the side. Spoon gravy over meatloaves and serve.